excerpt: Tulum is a town on the Caribbean coastline of Mexico’s Yucatán Peninsula. It’s known for its beaches and well-preserved ruins of an ancient Mayan port city. The main building is a large stone structure called El Castillo (castle), perched on a rocky cliff above the white sand beach and turquoise sea. Near the ruins is the Parque Nacional Tulum, a coastal area with mangroves and cenotes (natural limestone sinkholes).
detail_description: Tulum, situated on the Caribbean coast of Mexico's Yucatán Peninsula, is renowned for its pristine beaches and remarkably preserved ruins of an ancient Mayan port city. The focal point is El Castillo, a grand stone structure perched atop a rocky cliff overlooking the turquoise sea and white sand beach. Adjacent to the ruins lies Parque Nacional Tulum, featuring coastal mangroves and natural limestone sinkholes known as cenotes.
name: Tulum
address: Quintana Roo, Mexico

excerpt: Extensive menu of vegan & gluten-free bites served in a laid-back spot with a large covered terrace.
detail_description: Burrito Amor is a laid-back spot with a large covered terrace, offering an extensive menu of vegan and gluten-free options. The restaurant features homemade tortillas filled with various stuffings, including meat, vegetarian, vegan, egg-free, dairy-free, or paleo-friendly fillings. Emphasizing clean eating and fresh ingredients while delivering flavorful meals, Burrito Amor also has a full bar serving signature cocktails along with aguas frescas, coffee, and fresh juices.
name: Burrito Amor
address: Av. Tulum Mz 05-Lote 03, Tulum Centro, Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: El Camello Jr. is a popular spot in Tulum known for its delicious and affordable seafood dishes. Despite its unassuming exterior, the restaurant is always bustling with locals eager to savor their fresh and indulgent seafood offerings. The menu features standout items like seafood soup, tangy ceviche, shrimp cocktail, and whole fried mojarra fish that's crispy on the outside and tender inside.
name: El Camello Jr.
address: Carretera Chetumal-Cancun Locales 1 y 2 Lte 3 Mza 40, Centro, 77600 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Local bites, breakfast & cocktails served in a vibrant venue that has a beer garden.
detail_description: Batey Mojito and Guarapo Bar is a vibrant venue in Tulum that offers a lively atmosphere, local bites, and an array of cocktails. The bar features a beer garden where patrons can savor their famous mojitos made with freshly pressed sugarcane juice or enjoy other unique flavors like cucumber basil and passionfruit. In addition to its refreshing drinks, Batey also serves up delicious shrimp burritos that are a hit among visitors.
name: Batey Mojito and Guarapo Bar
address: C. Centauro Sur, Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Raw Love Cafe, located in Ahau Tulum hotel, offers a menu filled with gluten-free superfoods. The cafe is known for its standout dishes like the raw pad thai and acai bowl. Upon entering, visitors are enveloped in an atmosphere of love and tranquility, with an abundance of vegetation, friendly staff, and a peaceful ambiance. The cafe provides a complete sensory experience that extends beyond just the food.
name: Raw Love Cafe
address: Av. Tulum Mz 5, Lt 1 , local 21, Tulum Centro, 77766 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Matcha Mama Pueblo is a popular and picturesque juicery in Tulum, known for its vibrant and Instagram-worthy aesthetic. With locations in Tulum Centro, Aldea Zama, and the Hotel Zone, this vegan eatery offers beautifully crafted smoothie bowls and matcha lattes. The charming decor includes swings instead of chairs, cute wall murals, and a surfboard with the 'love Tulum so matcha' sign.
name: Matcha Mama Pueblo
address: Andromeda Ote lt 6, Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Coba is a significant archaeological site that may not be as famous as Tulum or Chichen Itza, but it's equally worth visiting. You can explore Coba with the All Tours Coba ATVs Mystic Adventure tour, which offers a chance to discover the ancient ruins and capture stunning photos. Following this, you'll enjoy a delicious Mexican lunch before embarking on an ATV adventure deep into the jungle.
name: C. Coba
address: 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Ola Bike Tulum is a popular bike rental company in Tulum, offering affordable and good quality rentals at just $8 USD per day. The staff, particularly Adan, is known for being friendly and helpful, providing maps and recommendations for exploring the area. Customers have praised the company's responsiveness to mechanical issues with the bikes and their assistance during unexpected situations like bad weather.
name: Ola Bike Tulum
address: Esquina Acuario, Calle Polar Pte. Manzana 4 Lote 2, Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Easygoing restaurant preparing classic pizza & noodle bowls, plus plentiful sandwiches.
detail_description: Palma Central is a versatile dining spot offering classic pizza, noodle bowls, and a variety of sandwiches. In addition to its culinary offerings, the venue hosts live music on Tuesdays and features an outdoor market with food stalls as well as a weekly clothing and crafts fair. The establishment is known for its family-friendly atmosphere and is easily accessible from various locations in Tulum.
name: Palma Central
address: Av. Kukulkan 6, Palma Central, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Taqueria Honorio started as a modest street stall and has now become a bustling taco restaurant. It is highly recommended by locals for its specialty in Yucatan dishes such as cochinita pibil, lechon al horno, and poc chuc. The family-run establishment offers a no-frills dining experience with seating at small bars and long tables under tents.
name: Taqueria Honorio
address: Satélite Sur 19, Tulum Centro, Villas Huracanes, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Aldea Zama is home to The Pitted Date, a popular dining spot for residents and visitors alike. This vegan restaurant offers a delectable breakfast and lunch menu, with many gluten-free options such as pancakes, waffles, and crepes. Whether you're a local or just passing through town, The Pitted Date is a must-visit for delicious and healthy meals.
name: Aldea Zama
address: Quintana Roo, Mexico

detail_description: La Hoja Verde is a popular spot in Tulum Pueblo, offering a diverse menu of vegetarian and vegan dishes. Located just off the main street, it attracts a steady stream of patrons seeking delicious plant-based options. From pizzas to chickpea bowls, smoothies to burgers, the restaurant has something for every craving. Despite its extensive menu, the food consistently meets expectations.
name: La Hoja Verde
address: Beta Sur S/N, Tulum Centro, 77780 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Mestixa Tulum is a unique dining spot that offers a delightful blend of Asian and Mexican cuisine. The restaurant prides itself on creating delectable dishes without labeling it as fusion. The ambiance at Mestixa is described as dark, funky, and artsy, adorned with dragon murals and charming umbrellas.
name: Mestixa Tulum
address: Av satélite Entre Av. Tulum, Calle Polar Pte. y, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Italdo is a must-visit spot in Tulum, offering a taste of Europe with its delectable baked goods. The bakery boasts an impressive assortment of treats, including almond croissants and their signature Black Croissant. Locals and tourists alike rave about the high quality of Italdo's breads. Whether you're a bread enthusiast or not, a trip to Italdo Pasteleria promises to be worthwhile.
name: Italdo Café Bistro
address: AV. 5 Sur Manzana 892 Lote 6, Local 7, La Veleta, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: OM Collective is a unique and affordable yoga studio located in the city center of Tulum. The studio operates on a donation-based payment system, making it accessible to all. It offers a variety of classes including vinyasa and acro-yoga, with a community-centered feel. Visitors have praised the amazing teachers and the diverse range of classes available, from morning vinyasa sessions to special events like Cacao ceremonies and Kundalini Sharing Circles.
name: OM Collective
address: Av. Coba MZ 09-LT 1-2, Tulum Centro, Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: When visiting Tulum, it's important to be a responsible traveler, especially when exploring the cenotes. Restaurante Agave Beach Club Tulum offers valuable tips for first-time visitors to ensure sustainable and respectful travel practices in Mexico. It's essential to be mindful of the environment and local culture while enjoying the natural beauty of Tulum's cenotes.
name: Restaurante Agave Beach Club Tulum
address: Av. Boca Paila Km 9.5, Zona Costera, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Jungle Yoga Tulum offers a unique experience that combines yoga, jungle exploration, and cenote swimming. The activity begins with a yoga session in the tranquil jungle surroundings, where participants may even have the chance to spot monkeys. Afterward, guests can take a refreshing swim in a cave cenote with provided lights and shoes. The small group size allows for a personalized experience tailored to the needs and desires of the participants.
name: Jungle Yoga Tulum
address: Unnamed Road, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: A highway runs through the middle of Tulum Centro, a busy area filled with eateries, bars and lodging options ranging from simple hostels to stylish boutique hotels. Schools, shops and service establishments cater to residents. A few small parks offer a relaxed venue to sit and enjoy some street food. Tulum Centro provides access to popular attractions like the Tulum Archaeological Zone and the SFER IK art gallery.
detail_description: Tulum Centro is a bustling area in Tulum, Mexico, featuring a variety of dining options, bars, and accommodation choices. From budget-friendly hostels to chic boutique hotels, there's something for every traveler. The neighborhood also caters to locals with schools, shops, and services. Visitors can relax in small parks and indulge in street food while being close to attractions like the Tulum Archaeological Zone and the SFER IK art gallery.
name: Tulum Centro
address: Col Huracanes, 77760 Tulum, Quintana Roo, Mexico

detail_description: Sabor de Mar is a charming, family-owned seafood restaurant located in Tulum pueblo. The menu features beautifully presented gourmet fish and shellfish dishes, including tuna sashimi, seafood and shellfish medley towers with avocado and seaweed in spiced salsa or broth, and the popular aguachile.
name: Sabor de Mar
address: Calle Júpiter Nte. Manzana 5, Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Don Cafeto is a long-standing Mexican restaurant in Tulum that has been recommended by multiple taxi drivers. It's known for its strong coffee, great food, and the popular drink called Chiagra. The restaurant is famous for serving staple Mexican favorites like enchiladas, fajitas, and appetizers that are described as absolutely incredible. It's considered one of the best places in Tulum for lunch or dinner.
name: Don Cafeto
address: C. Misión del Carmen Manzana 5°, Tulum Centro, Centro, 77714 Playa del Carmen, Q.R., Mexico

name: La pebeta
address: La Veleta, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Located in the heart of Tulum, Encanto Cantina is a top restaurant offering traditional and local flavors. Their menu caters to seafood and meat lovers as well as vegetarians, with organic and locally sourced ingredients. The bar serves cocktails made from fresh fruits like lemon, mango, and soursop, along with wines from within Mexico. Open only at night, this restaurant-bar features live music on Fridays after 10 pm, often playing classical rock.
name: Encanto Cantina
address: Av. Tulum 21, Tulum Centro, 77780 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Tres Galeones is a charming restaurant located in the heart of Tulum, easily recognizable by its vibrant pink flower-covered roof. The restaurant exudes a relaxed beach vibe with its simple decor and offers an array of delectable seafood dishes. From shrimp or fish tacos to marlin burritos, the menu boasts fresh and flavorful options for both lunch and dinner. Situated on Tulum Avenue, this casual eatery is celebrated for its mouthwatering shrimp burritos and Mexican street food.
name: Tres Galeones
address: 77760, C. 7 Sur entre 6 SUR Y CALLE 8 SUR, Tulum Centro, La Veleta, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: El Capitan is a popular seafood restaurant in Tulum, known for its delicious offerings and great service. Located along the main road Avenida Coba, it's a must-visit spot for seafood lovers. The flagship restaurant offers a variety of dishes, with their specialty being shrimp tacos and ceviche. Visitors also praise the fresh seafood soup and whole yellow snapper prepared by the chef.
name: El capitan
address: Av. Coba entre asteroides y mercurio, Tulum Centro, Col Huracanes, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Panna e Cioccolato is a popular gelato shop in Tulum, offering rich and flavorful gelato that allows the natural ingredients to shine. Their fruity flavors like guava, coconut, and passion fruit are highly recommended. The small shop has a few chairs outside for seating, and their affordable prices make it a great spot to enjoy delicious ice cream while watching the crowds.
name: Panna e Cioccolato
address: Neptuno, Av. Tulum 2, Lomas de Padierna, 77780 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Flora Spa Tulum offers a pampering experience that goes beyond just being a beauty salon, as it also serves as a wellness and spa center. The harmonious atmosphere and relaxing massages provide everything needed for a perfect holiday break to recharge energy. Visitors can enjoy drinks, use the pool and seafront lounge, or indulge in rejuvenating treatments such as sauna sessions, showers, cold plunges, steam rooms with scrubs, and relaxing massages.
name: Flora Spa Tulum
address: C. Centauro Sur, Tulum Centro, 77780 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Located in the heart of Centro, Cara Feliz has a great selection of books and coffee. It's perfect for digital nomads who want to work in a quiet atmosphere.
name: Cara Feliz Tulum
address: Calle Beta Nte. Mza 2, Lte 2, Tulum Centro, centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Casa Tortuga Tulum offers an amazing tour of four cenotes, with the option to hang out at two open cenotes afterwards. Visitors praise the beautiful space and commend the helpful guides. The $22 fee includes snorkel gear and a guide, making it a great value for an adventurous experience. The studio apartments are well-located and come with free bicycle use, perfect for exploring Tulum as a couple.
name: Casa Tortuga Tulum
address: Chun, C. Sian kaan Lote 21, CP, 77780 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Cenote Aldea Zamá is a hidden gem in Tulum, offering a tranquil and clean swimming experience. Despite some reports of litter, the cenote itself provides crystal-clear waters for locals and backpackers to enjoy. It's shielded from the sun and surrounded by a nice neighborhood, making it an ideal spot to relax on a hot day. This small but inviting cenote is popular among locals and offers a peaceful atmosphere away from the crowds typically found at other tourist spots in Tulum.
name: Cenote Aldea Zamá
address: 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Embark on a Tulum tour to capture stunning images of Maya temples against the backdrop of the Caribbean Sea. The compact size of this archaeological site allows for flexibility in planning day trips from Cancun, leaving time for other activities. From exploring Mayan ruins and swimming in cenotes to diving in reefs, there are numerous options for day trips from Tulum. The ADO buses provide convenient transportation from Playa del Carmen and Cancun directly to the Tulum ruins.
name: Tulum Tours
address: Guerra de Castas, Calle 2 Poniente entre Calle Escorpion Norte, Tulum, 77780 San Miguel de Cozumel, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Experience the Tulum Taco Tour for a delightful exploration of local cuisine and culture. Booked through Airbnb, this tour led by Victoria takes you to some of the best taco spots in Tulum, offering insights into the food and surroundings. Just like the stunning Pura Luhur Ulu Watu temple in Bali, the ruins of Tulum against the backdrop of the sea make for picturesque scenery.
name: Tulum Taco Tour
address: Chetumal-Cancun Huracanes, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Hydra by Gigi Pizzeria & Cinema in Tulum is a hidden gem with a simple outdoor terrace that offers a perfect setting for a relaxing day or night out. The ambiance is laid-back with wooden dining seating and soothing music. You can savor delectable pizza from their stone oven and even catch a movie at the cinema area in the back. The restaurant also serves amazing breakfast, fresh fruit, fantastic lattes, and attentive service.
name: La Hydra by Gigi Pizzeria
address: Calle Mercurio Pte., Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Tour service offering scenic bike adventures through the Yucatan's cultural & archaeological sites.
detail_description: Tulum Bike Tours offers a scenic and cultural adventure through the Yucatan's archaeological sites. Renting a bike is highly recommended in Tulum, providing an affordable and convenient means of transportation. The ride from Tulum Town to Tulum Hotel Zone presents numerous opportunities for picturesque stops along the beach road. Exploring cenotes by bike is also popular, with thousands of unique cenotes in the region offering diverse experiences.
name: Tulum Bike Tours
address: Kan Tours Main Office, Tulum Pueblo, Av. Tulum s/n, entre Centauro & Orion, 77760 Mexico, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Versatile tours centered on historical monuments, nature, culinary experiences & culture.
detail_description: Tulum Tours - Mexico Kan Tours - Eco Tours Riviera Maya offers a variety of tours that focus on historical landmarks, nature exploration, culinary experiences, and cultural immersion. The company is known for its commitment to nature conservation and responsible tourism. One of their popular tours includes a day-long excursion to Sian Kaan, where visitors can take a boat tour from Tulum to Punta Allen.
name: Tulum Tours - Mexico Kan Tours
address: Avenida Tulum S/N. Entre Orion y, C. Centauro Sur, Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Lively, unpretentious hostel offering an outdoor pool & a poolside bar, plus a shared kitchen.
detail_description: Che Tulum Hostel & Bar is a vibrant and laid-back accommodation option in Tulum. It stands out as the only hostel in the area with a hot tub, offering a unique experience for guests. The hostel's downtown location provides easy access to popular bars, clubs, markets, and the bus stop. Che Nights are a highlight, featuring Argentinian barbecue, pizza, beer pong tournaments, and karaoke.
name: Che Tulum Hostel & Bar
address: Calle Polar Pte. s/n, Tulum Centro, Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Fish tacos, guacamole & seafood towers served in a loft-style space or on a sprawling, leafy patio.
detail_description: If you're on the hunt for a vibrant seafood experience in Tulum, look no further than La Negra Tomasa. This lively eatery boasts a modern, loft-style ambiance complemented by an inviting leafy patio. Known for its eclectic atmosphere and upbeat music, it serves up a mouthwatering array of seafood dishes that are sure to delight your taste buds. Signature offerings include fresh oysters and the mar y tierra tostadas, which combine surf and turf on crispy tortillas.
name: La Negra Tomasa
address: Andromeda Ote 14, Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Cenote Cristal and Cenote Escondido are two lesser-known open-air cenotes located just outside of Tulum town. Cenote Cristal is known for its round and wide shape with a high diving platform, while Cenote Escondido is long and skinny, featuring a rope swing and abundant fish. Despite not offering dramatic above-ground views, these cenotes are popular among divers due to the underwater caves that can be explored.
name: Cenote Cristal
address: Km 223.8, Chetumal-Cancun, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

name: Cockteleria El Dorado
address: Carretera Federal Tulum- Coba km 0 +500 m, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

name: Tuk Tulum
address: Calle Neptuno Supermanzana 2 Manzana 2 Lote 2, C.P. 77760, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Tacos Many's Tulum is a hidden gem that offers amazing and authentic Mexican food at reasonable prices. The owner, Manny, is passionate about his craft and the restaurant is popular among locals and returning visitors. The al pastor tacos are particularly praised for their taste and juiciness. The menu includes a variety of options such as burritos, quesadillas, and fresh drinks.
name: Tacos Many’s Tulum
address: Barber Shop, Satélite con polar Enfrente de Eduardos, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Holistika House in Tulum offers a serene atmosphere with lush greenery, sound baths, and yoga classes. The property is praised for its beauty and trendy healthy cafe. Visitors can explore the outdoor museum with Instagram-worthy spots and enjoy various yoga classes along with delicious food and drinks. The place is perfect for relaxation, offering beautiful gardens and hammocks. However, some visitors have noted that the service was not consistent during their visit.
name: Holistika House
address: Aldea Zama, CALLE ITZAMNÁ NORTE Manzana 26 Lote 58, La Veleta, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: Ikal Tulum is the perfect destination for fitness enthusiasts and those seeking a unique getaway experience. Visitors can enjoy activities such as beach volleyball, Muay Thai training, CrossFit classes, salsa and bachata dancing, yoga sessions, rock climbing, mountain biking in jungle trails, stand-up paddleboarding on lagoons or at the beach, and kitesurfing.
name: Ikal Tulum
address: 5 Av Sur, La Veleta, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

detail_description: La Reyna de Michoacan is a popular ice cream and soft drink store known for its delicious treats. They offer a variety of fruity drinks in creamy and juicy flavors, such as lime and pina colada, at reasonable prices. The store is bustling with locals at night, creating a lively atmosphere. Across the street, there are great taco options available at affordable prices. Visitors highly recommend trying the pineapple paleta for an unforgettable experience.
name: La Reyna de Michoacan
address: Tulum Centro, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Visitors can snorkel & swim with turtles at this well-known public beach with tourist amenities.
detail_description: Playa Akumal, located in the Riviera Maya, is a popular public beach where visitors can enjoy snorkeling and swimming with turtles. The bay's waters are home to these beautiful creatures, making it possible for snorkelers to observe them up close as they feed on aquatic vegetation. The beach's name, which means "place of the turtles" in Mayan, reflects its main attraction.
name: Playa Akumal
address: Carretera Tulum, Yodzonot, 77776 Cancún, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: White sand beach with palm trees & turquoise water featuring casual eateries & sunbed rentals.
detail_description: Paradise Beach, also known as Playa Paraiso or Tulum Paraiso Beach, is a stunning stretch of white sand and turquoise waters located in the Riviera Maya. It's often hailed as one of Mexico's best beaches and is a popular destination for tourists worldwide. The beach boasts swaying palm trees, lush jungle surroundings, and nearby Mayan ruins, creating an idyllic setting for relaxation and exploration.
name: Paradise Beach
address: Quintana Roo, Mexico

excerpt: Shallow cenote offering clear waters for snorkelers with fish & sea turtles, plus paths & benches.
detail_description: Yal-Ku Cenote, also known as Cenote Akumal, is a large and shallow cenote located close to the sea, giving it the feel of an inlet rather than a traditional cenote. It's a popular spot for snorkeling due to its clear waters and abundant marine life, including fish and sea turtles. The lagoon offers paths and benches for visitors to relax and enjoy the natural beauty.
name: YAL-KU CENOTE Y Laguna Yalku
address: Calle Acceso Etapa H Lote 5 Akumal Norte, 77776 Akumal, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Scenic rainforest park with an underground river for swimming, a zipline & cave exploration.
detail_description: Aktun Chen is an EcoPark located between Playa del Carmen and Tulum, offering a unique experience for nature enthusiasts. The park features a stunning rainforest setting with activities such as ziplining, swimming in underground rivers, and cave exploration. While the admission cost may be higher than other cenotes in the area, visitors are treated to guided tours through caves and underground rivers with carefully placed ambient lighting creating a mesmerizing atmosphere.
name: Aktun Chen
address: Carr. Cancún - Tulum Km 107, 77780 Akumal, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Primate sanctuary featuring rescued animals & a souvenir shop with handmade indigenous crafts.
detail_description: The Akumal Monkey Sanctuary is a unique attraction in the Mayan Riviera region that offers a safe and enjoyable environment for animal lovers to interact with rescued primates and other animals. The sanctuary is home to a variety of species, including howler monkeys, spider monkeys, capuchin monkeys, lemurs, snakes, ostriches, zebras, deer, goats, and birds.
name: Akumal Monkey Sanctuary
address: Camino a Uxuxubi S/N, Predio Santa Pilar, 77776 Akumal, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Underwater cave system popular for snorkeling & cave diving, plus wildlife viewing.
detail_description: Cenotes Sac Actún is a part of the extensive underground river system in the Riviera Maya, offering a unique experience for visitors. These sinkholes in the limestone provide access to fresh water and are popular for activities such as swimming, snorkeling, and diving. The cenote holds the distinction of being home to the longest underground river and the second-longest underwater cave system globally.
name: Cenotes Sac Actún
address: Carretera Federal 307 (Cancun-Chetumal) pasando, Xel-Ha, un kilometro hacia, 77760 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico

excerpt: Ruins of a walled, ancient Mayan city, located on a bluff overlooking the Caribbean Sea.
detail_description: Tulum is a captivating destination known for its ancient Mayan ruins perched on a cliff overlooking the Caribbean Sea. It has been recognized as an up-and-coming travel spot, appealing to those seeking a more laid-back and trendy atmosphere. The area boasts a 2-kilometer stretch of pristine beach and offers activities like swimming and snorkeling in a serene setting.
name: Tulum
address: Zona Hotelera Tulum, 77765 Tulum, Q.R., Mexico
